\par\pard\plain \tx-480\tx0\ri-998\sl360\slmult1\ql\ltrch\loch {\f8\fs22\b0\i0\cf1 \tab Many of my other influences ranged from rather conventional, such as studies of chatbots, imaginary friends and computer-controlled competitive 'bots' in videogames\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f5\fs22\b0\i0\super\cf1 \tab  \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f5\fs20\b0\i0\cf1 Dom article\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f5\fs22\b0\i0\super\cf1 \tab  \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f5\fs20\b0\i0\cf1 ELIZA\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f5\fs22\b0\i0\super\cf1 \tab  \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f5\fs20\b0\i0\cf1 Passing Turing Test\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f5\fs22\b0\i0\super\cf1 \tab  \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f5\fs20\b0\i0\cf1 Zubek and Khoo \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f5\fs22\b0\i0\super\cf1 \tab  \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f5\fs20\b0\i0\cf1 Partington and Bryson\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f5\fs22\b0\i0\super\cf1 \tab  \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f5\fs20\b0\i0\cf1 Imaginary Friend #1\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f5\fs22\b0\i0\super\cf1 \tab  \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f5\fs20\b0\i0\cf1 Imaginary Friend #2\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f5\fs22\b0\i0\super\cf1 \tab   \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f5\fs20\b0\i0\cf1 Imaginary Friend #3\\end_Scrv_fn\}}{\f8\fs22\b0\i0\cf1  to the more outlandish, such as the history of automata as characterised mechanical (rather than electronic) systems\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f5\fs22\b0\i0\super\cf1 \tab  \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f5\fs20\b0\i0\cf1 McCorduck\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f5\fs22\b0\i0\super\cf1 \tab  \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f5\fs20\b0\i0\cf1 Public Domain Review\\end_Scrv_fn\}}{\f8\fs22\b0\i0\cf1  to the interesting reversals of characterisation in the literature on dehumanisation and compassion fatigue\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f5\fs22\b0\i0\super\cf1 \tab  \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f5\fs20\b0\i0\cf1 Bride\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f5\fs22\b0\i0\super\cf1 \tab  \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f5\fs20\b0\i0\cf1 Jones Fairnie\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f5\fs22\b0\i0\super\cf1 \tab  \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f5\fs20\b0\i0\cf1 Haque and Waytz\\end_Scrv_fn\}}{\f8\fs22\b0\i0\cf1 , which provided interesting models for Anne's (and potentially the visitor's) treatment of the 'spyrit'. In the spirit of the autocosmic, it was perhaps these less expected explorations of characterisation which were the most valuable to my work. A problem as seemingly intractable as computational character serves to benefit from lateral considerations: and it is one of these unusual approaches which forms the focus of this final chapter of the thesis.}
\par\pard\plain \tx-480\tx0\ri-998\sl360\slmult1\ql\ltrch\loch {\f8\fs22\b0\i0\cf1 It is perhaps the most important autocosmic inspiration for }{\f9\fs22\b0\i0\cf1 knole}{\f8\fs22\b0\i0\cf1 : one which has indelibly coloured its construction, fictive universe and thematic concerns. Above all, it is a specific embodiement of the general autocosmic philosophy; considering how human relationships with space, place and environment can possibly have something to tell us about their relationships with persons.}
